text:
you guys i swear i don’t run all these miles for anything except all the mother fucken truth bombs that drop on my soul in the process.•
•
when you run into fear you have to make a choice to either control the process or trust it. 
and  in order to trust you have to let go of control. 
but to have control means you let go of trust.•
•
the opposite of fear is complacency. 
the opposite of trust is control. 
the opposite of more is enough. •
•
i don’t know about you but in this life i seek fear, trust and enough. ❤️
#milesofhealing #chasingboston

"everyone deserves respect. we deserve respect." #respetonaman is a nationwide campaign against gender-based violence. the goal of the project is to spark a sustainable movement across the nation to eliminate all forms of gender-based violence in the philippines through campaigning for awareness, empowerment, and policy.

as inspired by the global #metoo, and #timesup movement and thailand’s #donttellmehowtodress movement, it will focus on bringing the issue into the mainstream and empowering women to rise up against all forms of gender-based violence.

in line with this year's 16-days of activism against gender-based violence, #respetonaman will hold a series of events and programs which would include two big forums, an online campaign, and a localized version of the #donttellmehowtodress exhibit.

#respetonaman is a project of the office of  vp leni robredo, un women safe cities metro manila programme, the embassy of sweden in manila, spark philippines, and #empower; supported by don'ttellmehowtodress thailand, cindy sirinya bishop, bdo unibank, sanggunian ng mga paaralang loyola ng ateneo de manila, osci (office of social  concern and involvement of ateneo de manila university), and power plant mall.

follow our campaign page to join the movement: facebook.com/respetonamanph

text:
hello to my followers, friends and family : )

my creative block is more than i imagined…… i have taken a leave of absence from social media to focus on the most difficult personal healing process, i could have imagined.

diagnosed with complex ptsd only a year ago, i am now experiencing an intensity of subconscious resistance to the psychological therapy or onion peeling process.  no easy feat tearing down a well armoured, inner child and psyche.  built to defend me against early childhood mental, emotional and sexual abusers, and the over whelming life long trauma around my #metoo struggles. 
a second chakra blockage of epic proportions, i reel, as i am reluctant to let go of my defences ….. my roar ! , as my badger spirit, did a great job of protecting me.  at times i had to fight hard, at times i fled …. more often i fought my way out of things.  even a black bear attack, badger came to my rescue.

take good care, as you journey in life.  take those early childhood attacks on your wee psyche seriously, as i am finding out it is insidious, and now proven to get worse in adult onset. with many known diseases and disorders coming to fruition later in life, as well as , cognitive impairment from the stress of abuse. #protectthechildrenfromsexualabuse 
my therapist has begun emdr work : eye movement desensitization and reprocessing.  what a ride.

eight sessions. four to break me open and poke around the bad memories . stirring me up to trigger memories / responses,  then four more to install more positive memories of myself .

informing me, it gets worse before it gets better : / …… i journey on.

i suspect, my art will be evolving along with me.

stay tuned.

big wild wounded woman hugs to us all xo

#complexptsd #survivingchildabuse #metoo #metoomovement #bullies #shunning #reconstructingmypsyche #woundedwarriors #creativeblock #compassion #posttraumaticstressdisorder #peaceandlovetothechildren #survivor #healing

text: this hits me in so many areas of my life. first obviously, being i am an almost 26 year old trying to pursue ballet and it's not a cake walk. but my work from home, my past of abuse, my marriage that's surviving on strings of therapy and group recovery, and the lack of being able to conceive children without some kind of miracle. all these things that people don't see but want to be strong like us, i have to laugh. (sarcastically) cause i personally wouldn't go through this if i had a choice and i am hoping to keep my son from the same fate. but ballet and creating my own business takes all my anger and hurt and pain and puts it towards me. i get to choose to work hard for something for myself. #avoiceandachoice #ballet #successquotes #life #hercrowningglory #killingit #inforthelongrun #metoo #hardwork

text:
******trigger warning***** this is the view from inside your car. i snapped this pic as you drove us to the second bar. 
the american flag, stripes of white and red, at that point in the night i had no idea i’d end up in your bed. 
my rape kit? 
doesn’t mean shit... because after 6 month past? 
it becomes trash. 
though the evidence isn’t allowed to last, i get to live every second of every day remembering what you did. 
to me. 
let’s face it, i was wasted, but america the beautiful? 
forgot the basics. 
that: 
yes means yes and no means no. “no!” doesn’t mean continue to rip off my clothes. 
yelling “stop!”, “please stop!”, as you pinned me down? 
did not mean, 
i want more so please don’t stop now. 
america! you so beautiful! 
this rape culture you cultivate? 
makes me want to be a man too. 
so i can teach my brothers, that one thing should not lead to another unless clear consent of yes! has been given, 
so that you can mutually begin 
the act of engaging in... .
.
.

text:
"panty portrait: cooch" from the panty project, 9 of 51
.

fiber art, archival pigment print on museum cotton rag, 
19 x 14 inches
.
the panty project is an ongoing social practice project. participants, womxn and those who identify as womxn, courageously share with me their stories of experienced gendered transgressions and violent aggressions, whether cultural and/or interpersonal. participants write a word or phrase onto the panel of their selected undergarment; i hand-embroider over their mark-making and photograph them as if they have been taken off. this work addresses the inherent misogyny within our language, and the consequential "essestializing" of womxn, which reduces womxn, and those who identify as womxn, to "less than." this work is about healing and transcendence. 
womxn's long-silenced voices must be heard.
.
#exhibition #msu #uniongallery #january #2019 #contemporaryart #art #womeninthearts #feministart #feminism #fineartphotography #photography #artonpaper #fiberart #gender #race #intersectionality #socialpractice #womensupportingwomen #womenempowerment #women #womxn #womensmarch #believesurvivors #mensupportingwomen #webelieveyou #metoo #thepersonalispolitical

"panty porait: cooch" from the panty project, 9 of 51
.

fiber a, archival pigment print on museum cotton rag, 
19 x 14 inches
.
the panty project is an ongoing social practice project. paicipants, womxn and those who identify as womxn, courageously share with me their stories of experienced gendered transgressions and violent aggressions, whether cultural and/or interpersonal. paicipants write a word or phrase onto the panel of their selected undergarment; i hand-embroider over their mark-making and photograph them as if they have been taken off. this work addresses the inherent misogyny within our language, and the consequential "essestializing" of womxn, which reduces womxn, and those who identify as womxn, to "less than." this work is about healing and transcendence. 
womxn's long-silenced voices must be heard.
.

text:
so i needed some time to process and react, if necessary. on a night in march 2009, i experienced another sexual assault, while out with someone who was my friend. when i woke up to pain and bruising on various parts of my body, i was in shock. but quickly realised what happened. i questioned why god let this happen to me again. why did i have to endure another one?! what the fuck kind of karma do i have and why can’t i get rid of it? turning inward, i stopped having fun, dating, exercising...living life. drinking and comfort food consoled me, but i always felt empty. 
i saw him this weekend. and instead of experiencing a flashback, anxiety, crying or retreating i ignored him. he  grabbed my hand to say hello, because i refused to acknowledge him. i responded with indifference. 
and was not triggered by his presence or energy. my friends were upset by his being in close proximity and i was fine. i’m still fine. 
in my growth, i understand why he felt it necessary to take what was not his. there was power and control gained by what he did. when i said no to his previous advances, that was his trigger. the assault was the result. 
it has taken a great amount of love for myself to arrive at this level of understanding, forgiveness, and resilience. and for this i am beyond grateful and beaming with pride. (2/2)  #shethrives #forgiveyourself #stillstanding #diamondstrong #badass #survivor #metoo #writeon #resilience #writeaboutit #writingistherapy #writersofinstagram #jemilada
name: Jemila Ada

text:

a $5 kit of washable sanitary supplies - shown in the colorful bags - allows the girls to stay in school for three years.

will you please sponsor just one kit?  help just one girl? text odflgep to 71777. 
leave a comment and come back tomorrow to learn more.

text:
hard to believe it's been 10 years since this dropped. like 10 full years. 
when you watch what's going on in the white house these days, it's hard to remember that things were ever different. ever more possible, ever more hopeful. every more anything-other-than-what-we’re-seeing-now... so i've been bumping this joint the last couple days just for the memories.  i actually knew a couple people that worked in this project—it's long story for another time from my "old life". maybe i'll tell it one day. 
anyway, this was probably the first "official" mixtape in political history for a mjor  candidate.
the man himself big rush had his name on this one. he's vanished under a cloud of #metoo rape accusations in recent years... but before that, russell simmons was as public an entrepreneur and ipresario as hiphop had. and even in 2008, he was an og whose approval still mattered.
so him and em's fave dj green lantern leaked this everywhere--datpiff, tss... every major blog had it at one point.

i'll talk more about this later. but google around. it's still up in a couple places.

it's worth running back!

#greenlantern #russellsimmons #barack #obama #yeswecan #mixtape #politics #hope #trump #hiphop #whitehouse #president #blackmusic #love #god #jesus #rapmusic #tracklist #deejay #dj

text:
my 2019 diary. a treat to myself for being accepted into a bachelor of health science (midwifery). my powerful sisters who have come before me and who will follow me mean that this is possible. a modern feminist is so much more. we don't just fight for ourselves, but for others, trans, gay, people of colour, indigenous rights. human rights are human rights. they don't come with colour, gender or a biological sex. "it took me quite a long time to develop a voice, and now that i have it, i am not going to be silent" - madeleine albright.

trump claims macron is predator, should not hold high office after leg groping incident⠀
⠀
it was a dewy eyed president donald trump that spoke to a hastily assembled press gathering earlier today, and there were clear signs of recent crying in his puffed up bloodshot eyes. it was also apparent that president trump was fighting hard to hold back the tears and to control his emotions as he spoke to the media.⠀
⠀
“macron is a predator and should not hold high office,” sniffled the president, “i have given what i’m about to say a great deal of thought before making this statement, but consider that i would not be doing my civic duty to the citizens of america, france and indeed the world if i did not come forward and tell of my experience with that beast.”⠀
⠀
president trump then went on to describe the horrific event he claims president macron of france subjected him to when trump was in france on a business trip. ⠀
⠀
“the circumstances were thus,” claimed trump, after blowing his nose into a tissue then dabbing dry his moistened eyes, “i had just flown into town for a meeting with macron. i was to be his guest for a couple of days. i can’t remember the details of where it was exactly or how i got there. i remember i had just arrived for the meeting and was feeling a little bit tired and disorientated from the flight. i do remember clearly that i had one beer.”⠀
⠀

a canadian man told me that men are capable of handling excess amount of alcohol, they are psychologically and genetically strong in handling alcohol but women are not. yesterday, i saw a beautiful dutch art by jacob savery in the art gallery of alberta that shows men going crazy, brawling and vomiting (in the lower left corner of the painting) while their wives are trying to control and restrain them. it takes even more psychological, mental and physical effort to control a drunk alcoholic man than it takes to handle alcohol. every individual has their own capability of handling alcohol, some women can handle more alcohol than men. anybody can feel sick and mad when it comes to excess alcohol, doesn't matter if it's a man or a woman. .
.

text: according to rainn, 1 out of every 6 womxn experiences sexual assault in their lifetime. there is a long standing debate about whether or not what a womxn wears indicates (somehow) that she wants to have sex. these are the options womxn have for underwear, ranging from full lace, thong, full coverage, cheeky, to "granny panties." the best part about underwear is that no one should be seeing it without your permission. people assume that if a womxn is wearing underwear like the pink cotton kind in the last image, they will be untouchable. those are the underwear i was wearing when i was assaulted, arguably the “safest” pair i could be wearing. so i guess the burning question is, "what kind of underwear will i be safe in?" and the answer should be simple. wear whatever underwear you want, because clothing does not determine consent. unless you say yes, you have not given consent; that is to say, there cannot be this gray blurred line with consent anymore. if a “yes” isn’t given, there is not consent to share. this is bigger than underwear. -sm ✨✨✨✨ ps: this post was inspired by an article; link in bio ✨ #cincy #cincinnati #humawomxncollective #feminism #sexualassault #womxn #womxnhood #metoo #underwear #womxnstrong #sohum

text:
my hair started falling out in clumps after my flashback nightmares started when i was 19 years old. my hair had always shed some strands, but it increased dramatically to handfuls at a time. as a child and teen, people often raved about my thick shiny hair over my sun kissed skin. being a kid who tried to excel at everything, i loved that my hair didn’t require anything to be noticeable. it was just me being me without any striving. i loved the ease of not needing to comb it or tend to it. my hair was an area of my being that felt best if untouched. free to be beautiful.

losing my hair while being tormented by flashbacks felt as if i was forced to sacrifice yet another part of me to the trauma. shame heaping on shame. and for me, shame turns quickly to hopelessness. so i cut my long shiny locks my freshman year of college hoping that short hair would mean less stress. it didn’t work. flashbacks remained and hair still fell out. i learned to ignore it, excuse it, neglect it, and tolerate it. it was okay enough, long enough, short enough, clean enough. enough hair to exist, but not the childlike freedom and ease i had once enjoyed. the less attention i paid my hair, the less i had to think about why it fell out.

what i didn’t know then (that i know now) is trauma triggers autoimmune chaos. my body was holding a level of suffering and torment it wasn’t designed to store. what i needed was to shed tears for the atrocity done to me, but because i didn’t know how to do that, i think i shed copious amounts of hair instead. 
this year i celebrate a decade of intentional trauma healing and major physical health milestones. i healed many of my autoimmune issues. and guess what else? my hair stopped falling out. and it grows thick and fast like it’s finally free to do what it’s always been made to do. and i get a big smile every time someone sees me now and says “i can’t believe your hair. it’s so long and full. it’s gorgeous!” oh yes. yes, it is. 😉
the little girl inside me who is learning to find her freedom again joyfully agrees. 🦋

name: Marisa Wandeler
tweet_full:
my hair started falling out in clumps after my flashback nightmares started when i was 19 years old. my hair had always shed some strands, but it increased dramatically to handfuls at a time. as a child and teen, people often raved about my thick shiny hair over my sun kissed skin. being a kid who tried to excel at everything, i loved that my hair didn’t require anything to be noticeable. it was just me being me without any striving. i loved the ease of not needing to comb it or tend to it. my hair was an area of my being that felt best if untouched. free to be beautiful.

losing my hair while being tormented by flashbacks felt as if i was forced to sacrifice yet another part of me to the trauma. shame heaping on shame. and for me, shame turns quickly to hopelessness. so i cut my long shiny locks my freshman year of college hoping that short hair would mean less stress. it didn’t work. flashbacks remained and hair still fell out. i learned to ignore it, excuse it, neglect it, and tolerate it. it was okay enough, long enough, short enough, clean enough. enough hair to exist, but not the childlike freedom and ease i had once enjoyed. the less attention i paid my hair, the less i had to think about why it fell out.

what i didn’t know then (that i know now) is trauma triggers autoimmune chaos. my body was holding a level of suffering and torment it wasn’t designed to store. what i needed was to shed tears for the atrocity done to me, but because i didn’t know how to do that, i think i shed copious amounts of hair instead. 
this year i celebrate a decade of intentional trauma healing and major physical health milestones. i healed many of my autoimmune issues. and guess what else? my hair stopped falling out. and it grows thick and fast like it’s finally free to do what it’s always been made to do. and i get a big smile every time someone sees me now and says “i can’t believe your hair. it’s so long and full. it’s gorgeous!” oh yes. yes, it is. 😉
the little girl inside me who is learning to find her freedom again joyfully agrees. 🦋

#traumahealing
#traumainformed 
#traumarecovery 
#metoo
#emotionalintelligence 
#thebodykeepsthescore 
#cptsdrecovery 
#cptsdwarrior

text: i’m literally a failed person on most days, well it certainly feels like that. i just can’t believe the stress and trauma i remained in all for the act of so called ‘love’ but it wasn’t love at all. i really thought it was and i wish it was, things wouldn’t be so complicated to fix if it was just for the act of love. except it was for the act of betrayal. it’s so soul destroying. it hurts me more and more everyday probably because more and more it’s not something i can talk about, to anyone really. nobody knows what to say and i don’t know what i want to hear but i want to hear more than what others have to say. i’m still confused and haven’t quite separated love and abuse. sometimes i thought i love him and then i know he made me feel like it was love. but i always remain back in the denial stage thinking i could’ve done more. i just know deep down at the time and even now that it was a situation i didn’t ever want to be a part of. my fear made me love him like he was something worthwhile—  #lawofattraction #perspective #emotionalhealing #mentalhealth #boundaries #checkyourself #mindset #lookwithin #selfcare #recovery #viewpoint #healingjourney #psychologicalabuse #aftermath #faithoverfear #humanity #lovehate #compassion #spilledink #mentalheathawareness #mystory #abusesurvivor #rapesurvivor #metoo #childabuse #trauma #molestation #thoughts #survivor #stockholmsyndrome

text:
have you ever had a liminal week?  one where the thin spaces, the grief and the cellular memories all seem to land together at the same time?  maybe it is the impending move of my bestie and her family, maybe it is turning a year older or maybe  i find myself at a halfway point for the journey.  too far to turn back from where i came from and too far to see the finish line.  monarch butterfly anyone?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
"did you know the migration period of butterflies and dragonflies is often so long that is often the grandchildren that arrive at the intended destination?" - miriam toews (women talking)

text:
ein 17-jähriges mädchen wurde vergewaltigt. #ibelieveher
der 27-jährige angeklagte wurde freigesprochen.
beweisstück vor gericht: ihre unterwäsche.
zitat seiner verteidigerin: "you have to look at the way she was dressed. she was wearing a thong with a lace front." ("sie müssen sich ansehen, wie sie angezogen war. sie hat einen tanga mit spitze getragen.") #thisisnotconsent ! das ist victim-blaming. das ist erniedrigend.
und mal ehrlich, heißt das jetzt, da "nein" wirklich "nein" heißt, dass das einverständnis frei aus dem nonverbalen interpretiert werden darf? wie kann aber meine unterwäsche etwas darüber aussagen, ob ich einer bestimmten person nahe kommen möchte? 
warum wird einem überhaupt immer in allem nachgesagt, man handle nur für andere?
warum muss immer darauf geachtet werden, nicht zu provozieren, nur weil die gesellschaft überreizt ist?
schminkt oder zieht man sich hübsch an, wird man immer gefragt, für wen man sich denn so zurechtmache oder wem man imponieren wolle.
jetzt trägt man also tanga, um vergewaltigt zu werden?
#endrapeculture
ist es so verwerflich, etwas zu tragen, einfach und allein zu dem zweck, sich selbst zu gefallen?
ich persönlich schminke mich, um mein gesicht zumindest semigern ansehen zu können. meine kleidung suche ich danach aus, worin ich mich wohl fühle. und oh! ich trage tangas. auch mit spitze. auch jetzt gerade - ungeschminkt, in schlafklamotten und mit zwei paar wollsocken, allein vorm tv. bedeutet das nun trotzdem, ich wäre jetzt einfach so mit allem einverstanden, ohne gefragt werden zu müssen? nein. ich trage sie einzig und allein, weil sie nicht rutschen und verdammt nochmal nicht, um leuten, die meine unterwäsche gar nicht zu interessieren hätte, versteckte botschaften zu senden. für solche fälle sind wir gesegnet mit der fähigkeit zu kommunizieren, denn so ein stück stoff kann nicht reden.
 #notaskingforit#novictimblaming#nosexism#nomeansno#feministmovement#genderequality#speakup#icantbelievethisstillhastobesaid #fuckthepatriarchy#metoo

text:
ironman arizona 2015
3 years ago today 🙏🏽
•
here is a little bit from my journal entry about crossing that first ironman finish line:
•
triumph.
maybe the only word i can use to describe this moment. overwhelming light and triumph.
•
this finish line was more symbolic of life to me than simply a race. three years ago…the same tears…the same hands holding my face…but it was a different girl…that girl was lying on the bathroom floor.
her truth was this…unloved…uninteresting…undesirable…untalented…un-strong…unworthy.
•
unless you have lived those truths to the point where it isn’t a fleeting thought it is your belief of yourself you can’t understand the depths that it takes to undo those beliefs. i don’t see any of those qualities anymore in this girl. but it was a battle to the darkness of hell and back to reach my new truths…
loved…interesting…desirable…talented…strong…worthy.
•
this race was for that girl.
i dedicate it to that girl who three short years ago was shedding the same tears on her bathroom floor and never in a bazillion light years could envision this moment happening. never. but it did.
•
and it was a battle of highs and lows on the ironman arizona course just as it was a battle in life. the biggest take away from this race is a new truth. 
a profound and simple truth…
•
the finish line is actually the start line
•
here is to life…love…adventure…miracles…magic…and all the wonders this universe, god and angels have in store…life is for living. so get out there and live.
•
because if i can do this…anyone can. and that means you.
•

text:
kesenjangan nilai kontrak aktris perempuan dan laki-laki tidak hanya dialami oleh hollywood. di bollywood pun demikian, dengan rentang jarak nilai yang sangat jauh berbeda antara aktor dan aktrisnya.

namun hal itu tidak dialami oleh abhishek bachchan dan aishwarya rai. tanpa tedeng aling-aling, abhishek mengungkap bahwa selama ini bayaran yang ia terima kerap kali lebih sedikit daripada nilai kontrak aishwarya rai. "dari sembilan film yang kubintangi bersamanya, delapan di antaranya aishwarya dibayar lebih mahal daripada aku," ujar abhishek seperti dilansir dari pinkvilla.com.

1. ibu abhishek juga dibayar lebih mahal

lebih lanjut, putra bungsu amitabh bachchan dan jaya bachchan ini juga menyebut bahwa ibunya pun dibayar lebih mahal daripada dirinya. meski tidak selalu, namun dalam beberapa kesempatan nilai kontrak jaya bachchan lebih tinggi daripada kontraknya.

abhishek menilai, kesenjangan nilai kontrak yang selama ini jadi perdebatan di india tidak berlaku di keluarganya. ia bisa menerima mengapa aishwarya dibayar lebih mahal, dan mengapa aktris lain juga dibayar lebih mahal daripada dirinya atau ayahnya. "deepika padukone dibayar lebih mahal daripada ayahku di film piku. kalau kamu punya kualitas yang mumpuni, bayaran tinggi akan mengikuti. tapi kalau baru terjun ke dunia film, jangan berharap dapat bayaran sebanyak shahrukh khan," ujarnya.

2. ingin perempuan diperlakukan sama

secara garis besar, abhishek mengungkap bahwa ia ingin semua orang di dunia memperlakukan pria dan wanita dengan setara. sebagai seorang pria yang memiliki kakak perempuan dan seorang anak perempuan, abhishek melihat betapa pentingnya kesetaraan.

kini, ketika india ramai dengan gerakan #metoo, abhishek pun menilainya secara positif. ia berharap dengan banyaknya perempuan yang bersuara dalam gerakan ini, kesetaraan dan keadilan akan segera jadi kenyataan di india. .
.
.

tweet_full:
kesenjangan nilai kontrak aktris perempuan dan laki-laki tidak hanya dialami oleh hollywood. di bollywood pun demikian, dengan rentang jarak nilai yang sangat jauh berbeda antara aktor dan aktrisnya.

namun hal itu tidak dialami oleh abhishek bachchan dan aishwarya rai. tanpa tedeng aling-aling, abhishek mengungkap bahwa selama ini bayaran yang ia terima kerap kali lebih sedikit daripada nilai kontrak aishwarya rai. "dari sembilan film yang kubintangi bersamanya, delapan di antaranya aishwarya dibayar lebih mahal daripada aku," ujar abhishek seperti dilansir dari pinkvilla.com.

1. ibu abhishek juga dibayar lebih mahal

lebih lanjut, putra bungsu amitabh bachchan dan jaya bachchan ini juga menyebut bahwa ibunya pun dibayar lebih mahal daripada dirinya. meski tidak selalu, namun dalam beberapa kesempatan nilai kontrak jaya bachchan lebih tinggi daripada kontraknya.

abhishek menilai, kesenjangan nilai kontrak yang selama ini jadi perdebatan di india tidak berlaku di keluarganya. ia bisa menerima mengapa aishwarya dibayar lebih mahal, dan mengapa aktris lain juga dibayar lebih mahal daripada dirinya atau ayahnya. "deepika padukone dibayar lebih mahal daripada ayahku di film piku. kalau kamu punya kualitas yang mumpuni, bayaran tinggi akan mengikuti. tapi kalau baru terjun ke dunia film, jangan berharap dapat bayaran sebanyak shahrukh khan," ujarnya.

2. ingin perempuan diperlakukan sama

secara garis besar, abhishek mengungkap bahwa ia ingin semua orang di dunia memperlakukan pria dan wanita dengan setara. sebagai seorang pria yang memiliki kakak perempuan dan seorang anak perempuan, abhishek melihat betapa pentingnya kesetaraan.

kini, ketika india ramai dengan gerakan #metoo, abhishek pun menilainya secara positif. ia berharap dengan banyaknya perempuan yang bersuara dalam gerakan ini, kesetaraan dan keadilan akan segera jadi kenyataan di india. .
.
.
source by : kapanlagi
.

text:
exposure to and the experience of trauma has been a part of the human condition since we evolved as a species. we are all impacted by cyclical acts of violence. however, there continues to be a paralysis in the conversation following human trauma. the recent national dialogue surrounding trauma, especially sexual violence, has proven that as a society and culture, many simply don’t understand or know how to talk about the aftermath of trauma…without shaming, blaming, invalidating, or placing the survivor on trial
.
.
trauma, in its many forms, is more than a singular event, but a force that firmly roots itself and can unravel many layers in a survivor's life. the aftermath of trauma can be more devastating and debilitating than the trauma itself. trauma does not remain still and moves with force and has the powerful capacity to reshape who we are, view of self and others, roles, relationships, the ability to cope, the ability to parent, and how we navigate through the world.
.
.
hey trauma, the day we met is an anonymous postcard project that allows survivors, as well those impacted by vicarious/secondary trauma (family, friends, or partners of survivors), to step out of the shadows of silence and give voice to how their lives changed....the day they met trauma. .
.
. ~dr. tama lane
.
.
#trauma #survivor #ptsd #ptsdawareness #ptsdrecovery #healing #breakthesilence #mentalhealth #mentalhealthawareness #webelievesurvivors #believewomen #believesurvivors #whyididntreport #imwithher #tothegirls #heforshe #metoo #malesurvivors #childhoodtrauma #traumapsychologist

text:
hey everyone. this is me! and it’s time to do a little bit of an intro. 🤗
my name is corinne, and i’m kicking off a chapter in my life where i focus heavily on my passions rather than what’s practical. 👩🏼‍💼
i’m lover of fashion. i'm passionate about human rights. i'm a feminist. 👫
considering all of that, i'm focusing on creating fashion portraiture that champions women of all backgrounds and celebrates their value and refusal to accept the status quo. ✊🏼
i'm heavily motivated by the red hot rage i (and the women around me) have felt in the wake of the #metoo movement. 🔥
with my photography, i invite women to sit for me in photo sessions that allow them to own their womanhood and their value, and to scream about it from the rooftops. 🗣
i want women to document periods of their lives, good and bad, their bodies, their faces, their heart and soul. i want women to see how beautiful they are today, because tomorrow we won't be the same. ♥️
i want women to hand their future granddaughters a beautiful image and tell them “this was me then.” 👵🏻
i’ve got exciting images on the docket and can’t wait to share.

text:
those 5 little needles in the ear can really  shift a person out of a negative space. auricular acupuncture for ptsd is truly magical 🌟
at our office we specialize in internal medicine and due to the emotional component of many illnesses we do lots of work on ptsd, grief, sexual assault, and trauma.
if you have experienced trauma we urge you to find an acupuncturists who is capable of dealing with these issues.
for those affected by natural disasters please look into acupuncturists without borders for free clinics in your area. right now, they have free clinics throughout the la and ventura areas.

#griefwork #stress #anxiety #assault  #metoo #southbaytotalhealth #healingjourney

text_retweet:
i am honored to be a featured speaker and presenter at this very timely + necessary event, which focuses on real questions + next steps following to pivotal #metoo movement.
•
we will discuss options for activism, healing and learn how we can take action to prevent sexual harassment & assault.
•
#repost @nadmax2 
we made some gains in the house and elected over 100 new voices to office. join me in los angeles 11/29/18 as we bring healers and activists together. we’ll hear from inspiring speakers and stand up powerfully.
•
location: the riveter 4505 glencoe ave marina del rey, ca 90292
date: thursday, november 29, 2018
time: 6-8pm pt
•
join us thursday november 29th at the riveter to discuss options for activism, healing and learn how we can take action to prevent sexual harassment & assault. we'll hear from powerful speakers that are helping people become whole again and stand up stronger than ever.
* * * rachel cook, seeds - founder of a techcrunch disrupt battlefield and techstars nyc startup using cryptocurrency to monetarily support those in need
* * * morgan mercer, ceo of vantage point - creator of ground-breaking anti-sexual harassment virtual reality training
* * * stacie yeldell ma, mt-bc, avpt - board certified music psychotherapist with 13+ years working with trauma in treatment centers and private practice
* * * amita swadhin, executive director of mirror memoirs - survivor activist who submitted testimony to reject jeff sessions' 2017 confirmation
* * * afterwards there will be time to share your story and interact with other healers in this space.
* * * 	#pantsuitnation
#makeanimpactmovement
* @seedsgives * @amitaswadhin * @badasserymag •
#metoo 
#healingtogether 
#marinadelrey
#losangeles 
#survivorleadership #survivor
#endrapeculture #empoweredluminary

text:
tomorrow is the day, maui babes! 🌴🏖🌊
.
in case this is the first you’ve heard of it, tomorrow the pearl projects (portland, or) and noonday collection (worldwide) are hosting a gathering in haiku for local women!
.
our purpose in putting together this gathering is to offer a time of storytelling and friendship.💙
.
the stories that we will present offer a thread that connects us to other women all over the world and to women in our own communities.
.
the pearl projects and noonday collection share a passion to see women flourish in every aspect of their lives. that is what this thing is all about.
the stories we’ll share have everything to do with the idea that when one woman flourishes, that she can effect true healing and change in her community.
.
we all want to be a part of something bigger than ourselves. noonday collection and the pearl projects offer a few ways to do that:
the pearl projects create resources and opportunities for women to gather together, to learn about god together, and to serve their communities in practical ways, together.
the pearl projects address some of the most pressing issues facing women today such as: what now, after #metoo (after sexual trauma). and how do i find meaningful connection with other women in my community? how can i help to make an impact on women locally in the sex industry? how can i let me life’s story become a tool for shaping my future?
.
noonday collection uses fashion (beautiful handmade jewelry) to create meaningful opportunities for artisans around the world. they empower women with dignified jobs so that the women thrive in their local economies. that means that children are cherished and prioritized (families thrive), and we get to be connected to their stories.
.
come connect with us and see noonday's line of fashion-forward jewelry and precious christmas giftables. hear from @jenna__hays (founder of the pearl projects) as she offers the beautiful stories that these two organizations represent.
.
can you come? 
consider this gathering tomorrow night to be causal, fun, and soul nourishing. great food and drinks and stellar company! 😍 7-9pm —>
#visitmaui #maui #mauihawaii #mauifood #friendship

text:
the swan, no. 1 by hilma af klint
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
this painting made me cry. it is as exhausting to be a survivor in the #metoo era as it is empowering. i’m trying my damnedest to open up the windows, and address the dark so that i may stand more firmly grounded in the light. i was raped when i was in college. my health, grades, and happiness deteriorated. i was a real shitshow for a couple of years. there are parts of me i can’t get back, and parts that are a little bent now.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i’ve had two poems accepted for publication in the #yanyr anthology, and i am so humbled, and so raw about it, and so proud to be where i am now. the editors at @rhythmboneslit created something momentous in giving survivors a platform to share art created out of such living, breathing grief. the you are not your rape anthology is heavy, and it’s necessary. writing about having been assaulted has been heavy and necessary. this isn’t my first publication, but it will be the first one in print, and i couldn’t be more honored, or excited to soon hold this book in my hands. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i am not my fucking rape. i am more than that unspeakable trespass against me. i am changed, but i am still here. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
yanyr now available for preorder, link in my bio.

text:
i have a great question for you today.  to what extent are you willing to challenge yourself?
is there something that you really want to do, but are afraid?
well today i challenge you to challenge yourself.  think of just one thing you’ve wanted to do, but have been hesitating, procrastinating or just too fearful.
-⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
this is the pic of me exactly two years ago. i met someone who was traveling to ireland and this was a place i’ve always wanted to go.  when i shared with him how envious i was, he said just book a flight and come!  oh sure...just book a flight.  i thought, who does that?  well, i did!  i booked a flight and in less than a week i was off to ireland!  talk about taking a leap of faith!  was i scared? hell, yes! but was it exhilarating? hell, yes! 
and not only did i fly to ireland on a whim, but here i am standing on the cliffs of moher almost 4 miles out! it was the most amazing life changing experience! (more about my ireland story in my book 😊)
-⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
so today i encourage you to do one thing - big or small and take that leap of faith!  every day is a gift and life is far too precious for us not to take that leap or make that change that will bring us the joy we are seeking.  so stop playing it safe!  what can you do today, that will help you grow and test your limits?
-⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
don’t hide behind fear of failure or the shadow of your potential.  find out what your capable of! i never knew i was capable of walking four miles on the edge of a cliff with no safety barrier in ireland!  it all begins with that first step!  who’s with me?  who’s ready?  xo

text:
prendono una persona, la costringono a piegarsi tra le loro mani come una bambola di pezza, la traumatizzano, le fanno pensare che qualcosa di così bello come il sesso, l'atto con cui si dà piacere e si crea qualcuno, sia un modo per umiliare, ferire e fare a pezzi l'anima di chi abbiamo tra le dita. 
e dopo tutto questo hanno anche il coraggio di dire che se l'è cercato, perché aveva le mutande con qualche centimetro di culo più esposto, mentre la verità è che se non sei degno di essere chiamato persona, se non hai rispetto per gli altri e se sei un porco schifoso, stupri a prescindere e la colpa è tua e di nessun altro. 
insegnano alle ragazze a passare inosservate, a proteggersi, ma perché nessuno insegna il rispetto? posso anche provarci con te tutta la sera e dirti no alla fine, posso negarti quello che voglio, posso negarti me stessa quando e quanto mi pare: due lettere, una parola, ma evidentemente troppa piccolezza nelle persone per recepire il messaggio. 
#no #thisisnotconsent #rapevictim #ireland #tanga #ibelieveher #metoo

text:
hace una semana un hombre fue absuelto en el caso de la violación de una joven de 17 años en irlanda. en el juicio, la abogada defensora, elizabeth o'connell, le dijo al jurado: "hay que mirar la forma en que estaba vestida (la víctima). llevaba una tanga con un frente de encaje"; y no solo eso, sino que en pleno juicio sacó la tanga en cuestión.
.
.
y a ustedes qué les parece, ¿una tanga de encaje justifica una violación sexual? 🤦🤦
.
.
.
#violacionsexual #violacion #metoo #thisisnotconsent #consentimiento #noesno #mujer #femina #woman #women #ibelieve #yotecreo #irlanda #dublin

text:
in my novel, we shall see the sky sparkling, lily is an actress working in london at the end of the 19th century, who gets sexually abused by her co-actor and employer, but finds it impossible to report, not just because of shame but for fear that her professional status as actor will render her claim dubious.⠀
⠀
read further on the history of rape culture and how women have always been suspect of some degree of acquiescence, and how rape trials have focused on the victims having to prove their innocence and lack of consent, more than determining the accountability of perpetrators in the blog: “actresses in the history of rape culture” https://buff.ly/2dkmdou⠀
⠀
 #historicalfiction #historicalromance #womenfiction #metoo #weshallseetheskysparkling⠀

text:
en ole jaksanut puhua #metoo'sta, koska... en jaksa. nyt kun on ollut jonkinverran puhetta kopeloinnista ja sen sellaisesta, voisin mainita jotain aiheesta. 2016 flow'ssa joku kertoi ystävälleen tarinaa kovalla palolla, käsien kanssa. hän osui rinnukseeni kämmenellään vahingossa ja hyvällä huumorilla vitsailimme tämän henkilön kanssa tästä sattumasta. mutta vitsit vähenivät nopeasti päivän mittaan ja varsinkin illalla, eikä kukaan sivullinen missään tapauksessa halunnut huomata, joten ongelma ei ollut vain itse ahdistelussa, vaan siinäkin ettei kukaan lähistöllä ollut suostunut auttamaan. harmitti etten jaksanut mennä katsomaan lana del reytä 2017, koska... en vain jaksanut, ja yhä toisinaan saatan valittaa tästä asiasta. tuntuu vain todella epäreilulta. 
tänä kesänä selkäni oli melko kipeä, joten kävin pitkillä kävelyillä, ja eräs kesäinen ilta istuin katsomaan auringonlaskua syrjäiselle uimarannalle. kunnes paikalle tuli vene, joka ensin kurvasi uimarannan ohi, mutta teki u-käännöksen ja ajoi rantaan. ja veneestä noussut mies meni vetämään käteen ainoan, virallisen rannalta pois vievän polun juurelle. mutta tiesin toisen tien pois, ja juoksin sitten kompastellen puhelin kourassa läpi rehevän metsän pois näkösältä. 
osasyy miksen jaksa kertoa näistä asioista on se koska jos kerron, usein kysytään: "mitä vaatteita sulla oli päällä?" "miksi olit siellä yksin?" "miksi sinä ... ?" ja huomaan monesti vastaavani: "ei, mulla ei ollut minihametta! löysät vaatteet!" mutta ei se ole vikani, että joku kokee oikeudekseen ahdistella, saada pelkäämään.

//
if you are in the midst of that messy growth part between caterpillar and butterfly, i just want you to know that whatever you’re doing is enough. whatever you’re not doing is enough. and if you feel like a failure, that’s cool too. it’s all apart of the process and you are doing great.
//
remember this...she believed she could, so she did. and so will you.
//

text:
there’s a new talk to be had, about how to be a conscious man who has sexual thoughts and desires in this day and age. men, we must learn how to integrate this energy and not shame it within ourselves.

we must make peace with that sexual tendencies and thoughts will come into our awareness, some you wish you didn’t have, and that’s ok. it’s all about what we do after they come into our awareness. in the ’what we do next,’ is where we can show our evolution as a species.  we must find the healthy place for this energy with someone we love or feel safe with. ❤️ i promised myself i would get bolder and speak my authentic voice!🗣
let me know your thoughts on this. 🙏🏼 i have so much more to say about this. 
sending you all an insaaaane! amount of love! 💛💛💛💛💛💛💛💛💛💛💛💛💛💛💛💛💛💛

text:
this morning as i got on the subway i almost immediately received this request for an airdrop on my phone. of course, wanting to respect privacy, i declined immediately without even reading it. it then continued to pop up on my phone a few more times before i finally read what it said. i declined again, thinking maybe someone was talking to a friend in some sort of joking manner (🤞🏻). then another one came through stating “you gay bitch??” mind you, i have a rainbow pin on my backpack so at this point i realize this person is in fact targeting me. it also became chillingly clear that, as i had my back to the last row of seats on this car, this person was also within just 10 feet of me. i declined again and the same message popped up a few more times, each time i continued to decline. then another message, this time reading “for real bitch how much to give me head”. this one came through multiple times and then another message “stop declining bitch”. i had two more stops to go at that point and it was all i could do to hold my shit together just to make it to my station. and then what about when i got off the train? would they follow me? am i safe? even as i’m writing this, my heart is beating just as hard as it was in that moment. this is a very clear form of sexual harassment. i’m sure i am not the first one this person has done this to and will not be the last. and who knows what else this person would have done or could be capable of doing in the future, or has already done in the past. sexual harassment/assault comes in so many forms and each experience affects that person in a unique way. there is no excuse for this, there is no “explaining it away” or just looking past it and pretending like it didn’t happen. this. shit. happens. every. day. when is it going to fucking stop?

#philly #gayphilly #queerphilly #byefelipe #queer #lgbt #lgbtq #gay #gaygirls #lesbiansofinstagram #instagay #truth #feminist #mentalhealth #resist #hardfemme #girlswholikegirls #endrapeculture #gayaf #gay #metoomovement #ibelieveher #girls #metoo #timesup #stopsexualassault #feministaf #respectwomen #mybodymyrules #septa

text:
so honoured to be asked to speak out in london next year.

for years i would hide in my past too ashamed to speak, to ashamed to be me, to ashamed to live sometimes.

this was a part of my life that i kept secret for a long time, fearful, scared, lost oh so lost.  i wanted to just bury it, bury it deep down somewhere so i didn't have to look at that part of myself ever again.  the shame i felt nearly burying me alive.

gratefully i am learning to stand proud.  i am learning to stand strong. 
before i entered this world i was already a lost scared child looking for love, looking for acceptance, family in whatever form i could find it in. 
i was vunerable and i was not in a place emotionally, spiritually or physically where i thought i had a choice.  i thought this was the only road that was for me.  this was the only road i could see.

and so began my life down this dark scary path.

i am grateful i have found my voice.  i am grateful that this once dark  path i could only see and once walked,  i can now walk down again,  but this time, this time i get to walk this path linking arms with others .... this time i get to  carry a huge big fucking light with me  and hold it so high, that it lights the paths of choice , love and hope for others to see who still reside in the darkness. <3 
#believesurvivors #believewomen #metoo #womenofcolour ##empowerwomen #standtogether #speakout #findyourvoice #nomoresecrets #nomoreshame #standforwomen #standwithme #standwithally

text:
[1.3] #tbt | marilyn and the ex-player are on a romantic dinner date. she’s wearing a pink jersey dress. these days, she’s getting ready for her big role in gentlemen prefer blondes. the ex-player is in the papers a lot, but not as much as her, and he wants to get to know her. how did you get your start? marilyn lies: in high-school! a talent scout…. did he fall in love with you? what’s your real name? when you don’t play marilyn, at home. she lies again: i’m marilyn, always marilyn.

norma is cornered. she’s incredulous. 
marilyn keeps revealing herself: i’ve always loved singing. it’s a way to cheer people up… to help them feel happy about being alive. but the ex-player, 9 years her senior, knows how fame goes: it’s never enough. people expect more and more from you. it’s not easy to get people to love you.

as she sensually puts her legs on his knees, between his thighs, the ex-player feels embarrassed, but he wants to have her. 
_______________

text:
my guest for the happy hour is blythe hill. @blythehill is the ceo/founder of the dressember foundation and is passionate about ending human trafficking. what started as a personal style challenge in 2009 to wear a dress each day for a month, @dressember grew beyond her immediate circle and five years later, thousands of people across the world have helped raise over $5m toward the fight to end human trafficking. wow!!⠀
⠀
one the show blythe shares some of her own abuse and how the #metoo movement and dressember are intersecting for so many women around the world. ⠀
⠀
if you want some practical things to do this year to help end human trafficking, this episode is going to give you what you need! ⠀
⠀
i'd love to hear what you loved and what you learned through our conversation! as usual, tag those friends that might love this particular episode! link to listen 🎧 in profile!!

then i thought... fuck that! and i’m so grateful i did! “buy some new lingerie put on some lipstick 💄 and handle it!” - you are now all privy to my ass kicking self talk 😆
.

if you’re in nyc tomorrow!! come join!! link in @freedomandfeminism bio! .
or download the kindle book 📖 link in my bio!!! 😱😱😱 $2.99 i mean... come on!! .
and if you want to plaster a giant grin on my face 😃 share a review!!
.

tess paras @tessparas is an actor, writer, director, producer based in los angeles. known for her roles on crazy ex-girlfriend, grimm, take my wife, tess is now creating her own space and is discussing her personal experiences. her current project, @thepatientsfilm , is a film about a filipino american immigrant family that is learning to heal through trauma in the time of the #metoo movement. the patients tackles the subject of a young woman who experienced a “bad fight” and the subsequent repercussions. it shares the story of relationships within the family, coping, seeking help, and supporting each other. an inclusive film, the patients holds a fil am main cast and a diverse supporting cast, with a crew behind the camera that are women, persons identifying as lgbtqia, and/or aapi. this is about sharing asian american and filipino american experiences that are not always told, validating our community, and being seen. to support, check the link below and read more about tess and her work. 
tess is driven and strong, taking up space and telling her stories. 
#intheheartstories #pinay #thepatientsfilm #filam #filipinoamerican
name: Jella Roson

text:
på tal om ledarskap! idag fick jag hänga i ett rum med bara män! för första gången under mina 6 år som våldsförebyggare med fokus på förväntningar på män var det bara män i rummet. och det var länsstyrelsen västernorrland genom hannahs och annicas ledarskap som fixade det!
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••inbjudan löd: ”länsstyrelsen har sedan 2012 arrangerat årliga kraftsamlingsdagar mot mäns våld mot kvinnor och våld i nära relationer. i år ägnar vi kraft till män om män av män.
män toppar statistiken över våldsanvändning mot både män och kvinnor i världen och även här hos oss i sverige, i vårt län och vår kommun. under #metoo vittnar tusentals kvinnor i vårt land om sexuella övergrepp utförda av män. vi läser dagligen rubriker om våldshandlingar utförda av män. hur väljer vi att förhålla oss till dessa fakta? är detta ett isolerat kvinnoproblem för kvinnor att hantera eller är även män en del av lösningen?
dagen bjuder på föreläsningar om maskulinitet, hur unga pojkar och män formas av destruktiva normer och hur man kan bryta detta genom sunda, goda manliga förebilder och normer om maskulinitet och jämställdhet.”
••••••••••••••••••••••••••••
och 48 nyfikna, engagerade och beslutsamma män kom. ✊🏻 dennis från @manforjamstalldhet pumpade oss med kunskap, utmanade oss med diskussioner och berörde oss med filmklipp som fullkomligt kröp in under huden av igenkänningen. 
sen fick jag dra mitt snick snack, det blev lite repetion, en del provokation men framför allt hoppas jag att det väckte en frustration och vilja att bidra till förändring. 
heja annica och hannah, heja dennis och heja alla män på plats! (nej alla män var inte på plats) #insidanboxen™️ #mänshälsa #tasnacket #stoppamachokulturen #hurpratardu

the bigger issue still is that requqlicans are willingly piggybacking this lunacy and abusing the faith of their fellow men while campaigning for the midterms. this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text: they say you should do something everyday that scares you. well, here goes.... 💖i am very passionate about creating a safe place for people to talk about their sexual problems, questions about how their body works, how it changes as we age and how sex is affecting their relationships. i know what it's like to survive sexual trauma and hate sex, then go through the process of healing and awakening to the physical and emotional joy of sex. but, let's face it. talking about sex is like talking about money. 😳 there's a lot of judgement. there are a lot of ideas about what is "right" and what is "wrong." there aren't a lot of judgement-free zones to get help and ask your questions. ❓i created that space. it's called qs for the sex queen. it's safe. it's judgment free. you can ask me anything. i won't shy away from it and i'll answer it based on my experience as a woman who has experience a wide range of thoughts and feelings on the topic, combined with the training and tools that come with being a certified life coach. 😊i'm proud of the space i've created. i'm proud of the first episode, that you can watch below. (put on your earbuds) link in profile 😱and... yes. i'm scared about being judged. so, please, do me a favor and if this makes you want to unfollow me, that's fine. my purpose isn't to make you uncomfortable. 💖my purpose is to serve those who need to have this safe space. i want you to know you have a place to go. a place to learn and explore that is safe and supportive. video link in profile #metoo #selflove #fun #love #kink #feminism #youtube #sexpositive #sexpositivefeminism #ownyourtruth

80% der alleinerziehenden sind frauen.
die fünf weltreligionen benutzen seit über 1000 jahren immer noch ihre macht um zu predigen, dass frauen weniger wert sind.

urweiblichkeit ist mächtig, fürsorglich, schützend, anmutig, weise und gütig.

this week’s digest considers, among several topics, how we care for ourselves and others. bots are becoming carers, companions, and drivers. the success of #metoo and female leaders in the art industry remind us to stick together and ask for help. many have come to california’s aid to combat its deadly wildfires, which appear to be partially contained. in this week’s essay, nina powers examines the correlation between increased illness and capitalism.

text:
#fastfashion #dior #highfashion #jenniferlawrence #fuckfashionthatcolonizes
#decolonizefashion #workit
#reparations #decolonize #create #imagine #resist

first, there is no one method or formula for determining reparations.

so much of the violence we experience is personalized. the violence we experience is always shared by other people and communities, yet how it affects us is embodied and related to who we are in this #earth walk. that's why this method was designed for people like you and #metoo and #decolonizethisplace. 
second, calculating reparations is always an economic and #spiritual practice.

above all, the spiritual dimension of this method is central, and #survivors must lead each initiative. the point is to foster #healing, not pay for therapy and legal costs, and give people the support we require to create solutions for ourselves and our #beloved communities. so, what does healing mean for you as a survivor of the violence you seek to stop? given your daily life and needs at this time, what do you need to put in place to learn and apply the method?

from a purely economic perspective, what aspects of healing can financial reparations facilitate? this question is the most direct, but it isn't as simple as it sounds. for example, you might #desire therapy and know that therapists cost a rate of, say $60-250 an hour in your town. what if no therapist in your local beloved community speaks your mother language of #zapotec or #lakota or #quechua and that's the language in which you sense the world? what is the #honest price tag for your therapy sessions if you have to travel three hours to see a therapist who shares your cultural, linguistic, #ancestral #perspective?

what else is at play when it comes to money? emotions such as grief and anger, fear and pain, shame and guilt always bubble to the surface when delving into traumatic experiences, and poverty is its own trauma. what can make this learning process a means of healing financial trauma in your personal life and that of your beloved community?

please share this with anyone and everyone. you’ll be surprised at the power you have when we work together. let’s get noticed!
.
we lose 25 orangutang every day due to deforestation. an area the size of a football pitch is torn down in indonesia’s rainforest every 25 seconds!! these rainforests are hotspots for biodiversity, and vital for regulating the eah’s climate. i say these words but to comprehend them is simply too much.
.
in the past decade, brands including nestle, unilever and mars have promised they would clean up the palm oil in their products by 2020 – but with less than two years to go, forest destruction in indonesia shows no signs of slowing down. that’s why we need to share things like this and put pressure on the big brands to make sure they put pressure on their suppliers.
.
palm oil is used in 50% of supermarket products including cosmetics – some of which we come across or use everyday like kit-kat, colgate toothpaste, johnson’s baby lotion,  dove’s soap, doritos, kellogg’s pop tas, ritz crackers, m&m’s, head & shoulders shampoo, and many others! these companies buy their palm oil from wilmar – the diiest palm oil giant in the world – fuelling destruction, forest fires and human rights abuses across indonesia.
.

text: ywca new britain's sexual assault crisis service (sacs) covers a 46-town region - all of hartford county, part of tolland county and the town of plymouth. we offer assistance to sexual assault survivors and their loved ones. these services are critical after such trauma, helping victims and their families regain feelings of independence, optimism, and hope. the advocates on staff are trained to work with hospital staff, the court system, public safety officers and other counselors assisting their clients. you can call our 24-hour english and spanish confidential hotlines for immediate access to trained, certified counselors anytime. #sacs#sexualtassaultcrisisservice #metoo #hotline #crisishotline #webelieveyou

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the start.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit the hijacked party of puppets is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the bombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on my bed.

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
at a hearing before the senate judiciary committee, christopher wylie described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters. the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like ‘drain the swamp’ or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the ‘deep state’ that weren’t necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement.

jon sharman
the independent

text:
press release
new york--- kr3t’s,  choreographers host a celebration for their 29th anniversary called “the east side story, peace in the east”

friday nov.16th 8pm show
saturday, november 17th 6pm hors d’oeuvres, 8pm show, 10pm #aarondavishall

in the past, life struggles taught us how to be content and grateful for the little we had.  people now have more clothes, digital gadgets and shoes than they did growing up, but they’re still not happy; and never satisfied.
this show looks at what results from compromising family values for material wealth and how it’s destroying our communities.  we will shine light on the #metoo movement, all the violence in the community and dance tribute for junior who was brutally murdered in the bronx, our goal is to send a positive message to everyone through the art of dance.
 in addition we are glad to have our event hosted by jason andors & imagine, who have appeared on hbo’s bad boys of comedy, comedy central’s premium blend, showtime at the apollo and bet’s comic view.  music by legendary re-mix dj ted smooth.
 five kr3t’s established choreographers will be presenting dance numbers. several have performed on world tours with artists such as #j-lo, #chrisbrown, #rihanna  #beyoncé, #ladygaga, #usher, #kellyrowland, #missyelliot, as well on tv shows like the grammy's the vma's jimmy fallon and much more.
our goal is to provide an outlet to develop dance and life skills that will enhance their lifestyles long term. 
no matter what the obstacles, our dancers
keep rising to the top #dancers #performers #directors #tv

text:
#loveitall

all the ups, downs, breaks and put-back-togethers.
each crack makes you who you are at this moment. 
it may provide you with empathy and understanding. 
it may create the great listener that you are.
it provides patience and support.  maybe even forgiveness.
it creates a lot of other things that are a part of us too...but for now, let's remember the good.

#acceptitall #understand #myeyesareopen #myearsarelistening 
#beenthere #metoo #istillloveyou

all the ups, downs, breaks and put-back-togethers.

it creates a lot of other things that are a part of us too...but for now, let's remember the good.

text:
we want to ask you to do something special today. ⠀
whenever a woman is confronted with feelings of self-doubt it is so important to have a couple of strong, independent women one can look up to. they can inspire you to become a strong woman yourself that approaches life with confidence.⠀
we spend years thinking we aren't worth much, simply because there wasn’t an inspiring and strong woman to show by her example that you can and will achieve anything you desire. ⠀
if you have a women like this in your life, text her today, arrange a call, send her a postcard, catch up with her over a coffee break. she is the kind of women who managed to break free from societal conditioning of competing with other women long time before you and i did. she is rare. tell her that.

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

at a hearing before the senate judiciary committee, christopher wylie described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters. the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like ‘drain the swamp’ or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the ‘deep state’ that weren’t necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement.

jon sharman
the independent

text:
it was bannon’s interest in culture as war that ignited wylie’s intellectual concept. but it was robert mercer’s millions that created a firestorm. kogan was able to throw money at the hard problem of acquiring personal data: he advertised for people who were willing to be paid to take a personality quiz on amazon’s mechanical turk and qualtrics. at the end of which kogan’s app, called thisismydigitallife, gave him permission to access their facebook profiles. and not just theirs, but their friends’ too. on average, each “seeder” – the people who had taken the personality test, around 320,000 in total – unwittingly gave access to at least 160 other people’s profiles, none of whom would have known or had reason to suspect.

what the email correspondence between cambridge analytica employees and kogan shows is that kogan had collected millions of profiles in a matter of weeks. but neither wylie nor anyone else at cambridge analytica had checked that it was legal. it certainly wasn’t authorised. kogan did have permission to pull facebook data, but for academic purposes only. what’s more, under british data protection laws, it’s illegal for personal data to be sold to a third party without consent.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
we are proud to partner with actors theatre of louisville’s humana festival in presenting the world premiere of lily padilla’s how to defend yourself, directed by marti lyons.⠀
⠀
addressing the silent and pervasive crime of rape on college campuses, this witty and essential work is also the perfect platform for our chicago audiences to further dialogue about the current #metoo movement in ending sexual violence and harassment.⠀
⠀
developed in our ignition festival of new plays earlier this year, defend will be a part of victory gardens’ upcoming 19/20 season.⠀

text:
blood diamond_maddy bowen (2/2) happy #monologuethursday folks! as the holiday season approaches, i feel like it gets even easier to get detached from the reality of the world around us - you know, everything sparkles and smells of cinnamon and we want to lose ourselves in that magic, beautiful, happy world that doesn't really exist. which is fine, don't get me wrong. but still. being my other job in the fashion industry i see this stuff all the year around, and sometimes i feel the need to bring things back to reality.
wether it's fur, or diamonds, or anything that implies beauty being at the cost of someone else's happiness, freedom, or life, we should take a moment and really look through that beautiful, yet deadly thing. and maybe, ask ourselves if there isn't another way to make the world function. because there must be. 
love,
#agirlfromtheislandinnewyork

text:
hace poco en irlanda se ha dictado una sentencia que absolvía a un violador porque la víctima, una niña de 17 años, usaba un tanga con encaje, y el tribunal entendió que esa prenda pudo dar a entender al violador que la víctima consentía.

una vez más (y ya llevamos demasiadas) las mujeres no solo somos las víctimas sino también las culpables. las culpables de ser golpeadas, de ser insultadas, de ser agredidas y de ser asesinadas. por ello me sumo al movimiento #thisisnotconsent y espero (deseo) que  alcance la misma repercusión que alcanzaron movimientos como  #metoo, porque ambos van de la mano.

y este 25 de noviembre, día internacional contra la violencia de género espero que haya una gran movilización, porque lo necesitamos. 
#thisisnotconsent #againstviolence #free #freedom #women #respect #equality #sorority #peace #metoo #feminist

text:
thank you  @cristina_the_activist - your words are crystal clear to those who are capable of hearing and for those with a conscience. the others will unfollow or spew some righteous, guilt-fueled vitriol. it’s expected of the weak. this post is for those open to change and embracing a life devoid of cruelty and torture. thank you, in advance for being open to allowing the compassion to drop in. we are what we eat. their suffering only becomes our own. think about it. 🖤🖤🖤———————————i snuck onto a noosa dairy farm yesterday. i wanted to see the babies with my own eyes. from afar it looked like the crates were empty but as i got closer and looked inside, there were day old babies huddled inside. it was 20 degrees out, had been snowing all night and here they were by themselves in the cold. so many of them were absolutely terrified of me - others would run up and start sucking on my fingers just hoping i was their mother.
some of them will be used in the dairy industry because they are considered profitable - others will be killed not too long from now so someone can eat their fragile body. 
this is animal agriculture.
it is not hard work, it is not a good job - it is selling your soul to profit off of others. 
it is separating families to make money off of their flesh. 
it is raping animals with your own two hands to keep their blood line going to keep your pockets full. 
it is mutilating babies and calling it normal and necessary. 
it is creating families, only to pull them apart.
the animal industry is nothing to glorify, it is nothing to be proud of. 
it is slavery and ultimately death.
this child does not belong here, but someone is paying to make this happen.. is it you?

text:
mgtow 101: personality tests

there are a few questions and scenarios leaders can use to find out how the members in their group think. let's say you are seeking a co partner, assistant, partnership or manager, rather than asking the same scripted questions, you can ask questions which shows a persons ability to think out the box as well as vet their ability to comprehend information. you can also get an inside look to their subconscious without them getting a sense that you are judging them.

examples:

1) if you could have super powers, which would you have?

2) if you won't the lottery what would you do with it?

3) who is the greatest predator to the human, shark or lion?

4) the question in the meme above, red pill vs blue pill?

all of these questions are fun ways to find out how deeply a person thinks, without them feeling defensive about the questions. these questions may seem simple but it will literally give you insights to the depths of the mind, no matter how deep or shallow.

as an example, if i asked the question to a group of 30 people, i would easily be able to eliminate anyone who answered blue pill for a partnership, because it would show a lack of depth and comprehension. with the knowledge we all have today, everyone could be a billionaire if they could take the current knowledge with you into the past.

a simple person would say knowledge is just what you learned by being educated. however an outside the box thinker could look at it and pull a back to the future move, taking the almanac, championship winning teams and lottery numbers back in the past with you. you could even set yourself up to be viewed as a god on earth by predicting all types of events like 9/11, presidential elections, terrorist attacks, natural disasters and much more. these questions show how deep one is able to think.

text:
latin american cultural week features a number of jazz-related and new music events, in support of the #metoo #yotambién movement, including encuentro nyc (encounter nyc) colombian music festival, saturday, november 17 - 6:45pm set 1, 8:15pm set 2 - "roots part 1: spain, a multicultural encuentro” at id studio theater, 311 east 140th street, bronx (4, 5, or 6 train to 138 street station), nyc. 
tickets in advance, sets 1 and 2 $30 per set (includes pre-concert reception),$10 post-concert dance party with food for sale and recorded music. 
encuentro nyc colombian music festival at id studio theater, with music and dance highlighting the history of colombian music. part 1 of the roots series traces colombian joropo to its spanish and indigenous roots with guests rebeca tomás/a palo seco flamenco company with artists gregorio uribe (accordion, big band), daniel fetecua (dance), pablo mayor (piano, composition) and the folklore urbano nyc trio. uribe is a well-known songwriter, composer, and performer, all in new music, as is mayor, creator of the festival, pianist, and composer. they present a new vision of colombian folklore, as astor piazzolla did with tango. their music, though not jazz per se, presents elements of colombian music and jazz.

text:
in 2014, steve bannon – then executive chairman of the “alt-right” news network breitbart – was christopher wylie’s boss. and robert mercer, the secretive us hedge-fund billionaire and republican donor, was cambridge analytica’s investor. and the idea they bought into was to bring big data and social media to an established military methodology – “information operations” – then turn it on the us electorate.

cambridge analytica’s parent company, scl, had won contracts with the us state department and was pitching to the pentagon, and wylie was genuinely freaked out. - it’s insane, he told me one night. - the company has created psychological profiles of 230 million americans. and now they want to work with the pentagon? it’s like nixon on steroids.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
una #historiadebuenosaires
#memoria, #resistencia y #amor.

no podía irme de la #capitalfederalargentina sin pasar por esta puerta. en este número de avenida #rivadavia yo viví 3 meses, la primera vez que estuve en #buenosaires. es una casona #antigua de estilo #frances transformada en hostal pensión. el administrador era un hombre de 65 años, con una diferencia de edad para ser mi padre y mi abuelo al mismo tiempo. 
un día, mientras yo estaba en la #cocina, se acercó a mi y dándome una palmada en el trasero me dijo:"con ese culo, vives aquí gratis. ya sabes cual es mi habitación." yo salí callada y sin mirarlo, tropezando con la ira y la vergüenza. en los días siguientes, la cosa se puso peor. me sentía siempre observada, aunque no hubiera nadie. el #viejo se aparecía  mientras colgaba mi #ropa en el techo, para tocar mis calcetines y oler mis calzones.

no era por ser #bonita, sino por ser sola y extranjera. a los acosadores les excita la vulnerabilidad.

un día de #julio, llegué tarde en la noche y me estaba esperando. fue breve y claro: "te acostás conmigo o te vas". de nada valía decir que había pagado mi mes por adelantado y tenía derechos como inquilina. hice mi bolso y me fui.

esa #noche hacía frío y me quede en la estación del #subte catedral, rodeada de hombres #homeless. tenía miedo de quedarme dormida y que me atacaran.

caminé para no congelarme. llegué a la peatonal #lavalle y vi el letrero del hotel orei. toqué el timbre. me abrió la recepcionista de turno, una mujer delgada y morena, de pelo rizado. me dijo que estaba lleno. me puse a llorar, le conté lo que pasó. me hizo pasar, me preparó un mate y me dejó dormir en su cama. al día siguiente fui a trabajar, pedí un adelanto y me quedé ahí hasta que conseguí otra pensión en el barrio del #congreso.

lo cuento ahora porque lo enfrenté y soy más libre cuando rompo el silencio y me hago más grande ante la adversidad si bailo en la cara de mis miedos. 
#acososexual #violenciadegenero #violenciamachista #patriarcado #amitambien #metoo #amigayotecreo #yotecreo #historiasdemujeres #miprimeracoso
