text:
14-nov-2018:  seminar on 'women of marginalised communities: concerns about exclusion' held in amu

aligarh, #november 14: #women have rights equal to that of men, but they continue to face disparity with unequal treatments and perceptions wholly or partly due to their gender, said prof zakia athar siddiqui, former director, advanced centre for women's studies, aligarh muslim university (amu), while delivering the keynote address in the indian council of social science research (icssr) sponsored national seminar on 'women of marginalised communities: concerns about exclusion' at the #arts faculty lounge.

in the seminar organised by the advanced centre for women's studies, prof zakia pointed out that we need to focus on how to help women to overcome vulnerabilities and shape their destinies in the national #growth story. "to help women of marginalised communities, we need to understand that equality for women is progress for all," she said adding that gender equality, women empowerment, women rights and the eradication of poverty are essential to economic and social development.

mr nizam pasha, advocate, supreme court of india said that women, across castes and classes, are marginalised, even if the degree varies. speaking on the #metoo movement, he pointed out that the campaign needs to have representations from dalit, bahujan, adivasi and other marginalised women. "let us build more resources and support for the most vulnerable and marginalised as any campaign should not treat the most vulnerable as just an afterthought," he said.

mr pasha also spoke on better enforcement of sexual harassment laws and setting up of tribunals for women in the informal sector.

quoting swami vivekananda, prof akbar husain, dean, faculty of social sciences said, "there is no chance of the welfare of the world unless the condition of women is improved." he pointed out, "women are all powerful if they have strong mind, confidence in their body language and maturity in handling relationships. empowerment is an internal attribute. a woman may feel empowered if she is contended with herself in physical, emotional, mental, social and spiritual terms."

text:
night two.

fear.

i fear womxn.

the emotional abusers in my life were womxn. the ones who psychologically tortured me and gaslighted me as a child were womxn.

it was womxn who got into arguments over me, my health, and took away autonomy.

mostly womxn who set ultimatums upon me. snapped at me. took my things away from me. discarded me. projected onto me.

while mxn have been the sexual abusers in my life. takers. controllers. enforcers. arguing with the womxn about how to handle me. or, in the case of my parents, silently agreeing and allowing the mother to go off in rages. screaming at me.

screaming at me until i had a meltdown or cut.

then the relief of household silence and the pain from my fresh lacerations.

i had an immensely difficult childhood, but on the outside, looking in.. i was well fed after the homeless cycle was broken.
i had lots and lots of toys and video games. clothes. furniture.
i had access to the internet (but was spied on a lot..).
i had education. i went to college. in fact, going to college was how i escaped.

then my parents didn't talk to me much after that. i became even more invisible.

yeah i was loving growing up but i was also tortured and isolated while being subjected to anger, control, and emotional intensity that to this day.. to this very fucking day.. affects how i can socialize and step up in the world.

it sounds ableist outside of this context... but i can't handle people who are intense, angry, or who have frightening mental illness symptoms. i always wind up triggered and feeling like i need to hide.

the paranoia begins.
the fear.
the dreams.
the switching of my alters.
the grief.

i miss my mom. i never really had one. my mother was a shell of her traumas. i remember maybe twice that i saw the part of her that she was protecting from everyone, 27/7.

text:
this picture is about an incident that happened on 23 october.
on 23 october tamil nadu woke up to something that should've stunned it to shame. there is a village called thalavaipatti, there a 13 year old girl named rajalakshmi was beheaded by her neighbour dinesh kumar. she had allegedly spurned his advances. this happened when the #metoo campaigns were going viral, and yet nobody seemed to notice such incident. what happened was, she was sexually harassed by him previously. she even told this to her parents but they couldnt do anything as they were from a dalit family and he was from a dominant caste. that day when chinnaponnu(her mother) abd rajalakshmi were stringing flowers, he came there with sickle and beheaded her inspite of chinnaponnu's intervention. then he headed home with her head where his wife sarada advised him to discard it elsewhere. subsequently they went to police station together and surrendered. sarada convinced the police that he was mentally ill but it was just a plot to save her husband.during the investigation police made it clear that he was mentally and physically sound. the police see this as a caste crime whereas the society sees it as a sex crime. in my opinion its both. now he can come oug on bail, which should not happen. in my opinion the case should be tried under posco act (death penalty). it is such a shame that we all failed to notice such a horrible incident. women have always been worshipped in india and even been the victims of rape, acid attacks and everything. all these put us in shame. something has to be done and put an end to this cruelty . imaginge the state of the parents who lost theif daughter. i want all of us to join our hands together and we might be able stop all this in future. we need justice for rajalakshmi

text_retweet:
#repost @surya.ganapathy (@get_repost)
・・・
harrassment of any form is wrong. be it physical or emotional. the idea of sex & consent are mutually exclusive. there can’t be sex without consent. because sex without consent, is not sex—it’s rape, and rapes happen not only in work places , even in relationships and marriages.

we all know that the #metoo movement speaks of the widespread prevalence of sexual assault and harassment, especially in the workplace. it's been a revelation in our society, where many fearless women and few men who've been affected directly, have opened up in public, to stop the entitlement that comes with power of position, the wrongdoer holds, and the deragatory conduct & demeanor the victim gets subjected to.to keep the workplace, a purely professional place of choice. 
whether you're speaking out as part of the #metoo movement or holding on to your story, every single person deserves to feel safe, be happy and live past the physical/mental trauma they've been part of.

easier said that done, living in a society which keeps reminding us of the past we want to forget. however by making a conscious effort, we can get back to living the life we deserve, happy, rejoiceful, one that feels good from the inside. but for that, we need to heal. we need to understand that the past doesn't defile our honour nor define who we are, and what matters is how we want to live in the present leading upto the future.

what better way to heal than talk to someone who truly understands and is qualified to help without passing judgements. :) whoever you're, if you have a story to share and heal from, use my code "metoosurya" to avail a free counseling session with an expert on beamitlive from the smile again foundation. 😊

we are here, we are listening. spread the word and know that you're not alone! 
code link in bio! 🤗
name: The Smile Again Foundation

text:
yesterday was an amazing day of shedding the stigma of being abused by breaking my silence. 🙏
•
with my supportive and wonderful husband at my side, i travelled around london to guest on two shows. 🚂🚆
•
this is me outside the bbc, moments before entering to record with @annalouiseradio for her podcast, airing in early 2019. 🎙️
•
earlier in the day, i recorded with @eastlondonradio 🎙️
•
it's times like these that i remember how far i've come. i'm living the dream, really. not just because i am speaking up and wonderful people are supporting me in my mission, but i have managed to turn the worst 10 years of my life into something positive. 💪
•
i wouldn't be who i am today, with this mission, helping others to build a life of value, if i hadn't been forced to do the same for myself years ago. this is my purpose in life, and i welcome it with open arms. 🙌
•
i am my own hero; a warrior because of my abuse, not despite it. i will spend my life leading this charge, and i'll do it with a sense of euphoria, grateful for all those who cross my path to help me. ❤️
•
#changeyourlife #survivor #abuse #abusesurvivor #noexcuses #metoo #radio #podcasts #breakthestigma #breakthesilence #letstalkaboutit

text:
se on siinä!!! 💖 @suostumus2018-aloite ylitti juuri 50 000 allekirjoituksen rajan. nyt aloite voidaan viedä uudelle eduskunnalle heti ensi kevään vaalien jälkeen!

kiitos tästä kuuluu jokaiselle aloitetta tukeneelle ja kampanjatyötä tehneelle - ennen kaikkea 50 000 upealle allekirjoittajalle! ilman teitä emme olisi kirjaimellisesti pystyneet tähän. me olemme yhdessä osoittaneet, että #metoo-liikkeellä on todellakin voimaa kääntää suomen suuntaa!

tämän eduskunnan enemmistö ei halunnut edistää tätä aloitetta. siksi on tärkeää tehdä seuraavasta eduskunnasta edistyksellisempi! näin varmistetaan, että aloite saadaan vietyä osaksi suomen lakia:

1. jokainen tukija tekee aloitteesta ja sen tavoitteista entistä vakuuttavamman, joten allekirjoitusten kerääminen jatkuu edelleen!
2. allekirjoititko jo aloitteen? kerro julkisesti, että haluat äänestää ensi kevään vaaleissa vain sellaista puoluetta, joka lupaa edistää aloitetta.
3. pyydä puolueita ja ehdokkaita sitoutumaan aloitteen tavoitteisiin. haasta heidät tukemaan aloitetta  vaikka täällä tai twitterissä - näin viesti leviää!

ei tarkoittaa ei ja vain kyllä tarkoittaa kyllä. me haluamme, että suomen laki tunnistaa tämän perusasian ja suojelee jokaisen itsemääräämisoikeutta. siksi raiskauksen määritelmä on korjattava suostumuksen puutteeseen perustuvaksi.

oletko samaa mieltä? allekirjoita aloite ja jaa viestiä eteenpäin! linkki löytyy biosta. 
#suostumus #suostumus2018 #feminismi #tasaarvo #politiikka #vaalit #eduskunta #jokuraja #metoo #memyös

text:
часть і .
🌟анималистический принт
этой осенью никуда не скрыться от обилия анималистических принтов. живописные пятна шкур леопарда, оцелота, зебры и тигра густо покрыли подиумы четырех главных модных столиц мира. особенно эффектно выглядят нетрадиционные цветовые сочетания "хищных" окрасов с розовым, малиновым или алым. .
🌟логотипы
начавшаяся несколько сезонов назад лихорадка под названием "логомания" в новом сезоне сбавлять оборотов не собирается. не остались к ней равнодушны наступающей осенью даже такие стойкие к массовым тенденциям бренды как max mara и prada. .
🌟кейпы
loewe, saint laurent, isabel marant и missoni знают толк в правильной верхней одежде на осень. на смену узким пальто и пиджакам, словно снятым с мужского плеча приходят просторные и роскошные кейпы. снова одежда супергероев, оперных певцов и монахов-капуцинов будет исправно работать на модной службе. .
🌟многослойность
многослойность нельзя назвать чистым трендом этой осени. как только наступают холода, самым естественным образом наряды начинают сползаться в один большой текстильный "пирог". главное отличие этого сезона - самые "вкусные" сочетания фактур. нейлон с мехом или шерстью, бархат и кожа. .
🌟платья из кожи
кожаные наряды в эпоху #metoo выглядят настоящими модными латами и униформой разгневавшихся доминатрикс. на поясе или нет, длинные или минимально короткие, мрачновато черные или жизнерадостно оранжевые - без них модный пазл этой осени не сложится.

#трендыосени2018 #трендызимы2019 #молокодресс #тренды #стиль #мода

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
there is nothing more beautiful than watching someone concentrate on creating something, unmindful of what goes on around them. and as we all already know, most women, especially those in rural areas, do not sit idle for even a single minute. 
i watched fascinated as this village woman industriously wove dried reed into a basket. with due respect, i omitted capturing her face, as even though i had asked for her consent to click the picture, she had no idea of the geographical extent to which this picture could be viewed, and it would mean my exploiting her lack of this knowledge.....with the current #metoo campaign, it is a welcome time to revisit our meaning of #consent
to me it means a shared similar understanding of what is about to occur or is occurring. if one party thinks differently, then that is not consent....

text:
for those 87 million people probably wondering what was actually done with their data, i went back to christopher wylie, the ex-cambridge analytica employee who blew the whistle on the company’s problematic operations in the observer. according to wylie, all you need to know is a little bit about data science, a little bit about bored rich women, and a little bit about human psychology.

step one, he says, over the phone as he scrambles to catch a train: - when you’re building an algorithm, you first need to create a training set. that is: no matter what you want to use fancy data science to discover, you first need to gather the old-fashioned way. before you can use facebook likes to predict a person’s psychological profile, you need to get a few hundred thousand people to do a 120-question personality quiz.

the “training set” refers, then, to that data in its entirety: the facebook likes, the personality tests, and everything else you want to learn from. most important, it needs to contain your “feature set”: - the underlying data that you want to make predictions on, wylie says. - in this case, it’s facebook data, but it could be, for example, text, like natural language, or it could be clickstream data – the complete record of your browsing activity on the web. - those are all the features that you want to [use to] predict. at the other end, you need your target variables, the things that you’re trying to predict for. so in this case, personality traits or political orientation, or what have you.

alex hern
the guardian

text:
for those 87 million people probably wondering what was actually done with their data, i went back to christopher wylie, the ex-cambridge analytica employee who blew the whistle on the company’s problematic operations in the observer. according to wylie, all you need to know is a little bit about data science, a little bit about bored rich women, and a little bit about human psychology.

step one, he says, over the phone as he scrambles to catch a train: - when you’re building an algorithm, you first need to create a training set. that is: no matter what you want to use fancy data science to discover, you first need to gather the old-fashioned way. before you can use facebook likes to predict a person’s psychological profile, you need to get a few hundred thousand people to do a 120-question personality quiz.

the “training set” refers, then, to that data in its entirety: the facebook likes, the personality tests, and everything else you want to learn from. most important, it needs to contain your “feature set”: - the underlying data that you want to make predictions on, wylie says. - in this case, it’s facebook data, but it could be, for example, text, like natural language, or it could be clickstream data – the complete record of your browsing activity on the web. - those are all the features that you want to [use to] predict. at the other end, you need your target variables, the things that you’re trying to predict for. so in this case, personality traits or political orientation, or what have you.

alex hern
the guardian

text:
mother me too
40 x 50 cm

everyone knows what mother nature represents. she’s every plant, vine, and flower, every living animal, big and small, every rock, mountain, ocean, and creek. she’s everything the earth has ever given us. yet every day we as a species gradually destroy her. the business model based on monetary gain has ruined our connection with nature. so we dump our waste in the oceans, we fill our skies with smog and toxins, we slaughter animals in unimaginable numbers, we destroy acres of precious rainforests, and all of this for corporate profit.

after decades of perpetual torture, mother nature has lost her mind. blinded and intoxicated by anger she goes on a rampage destroying even that what she created and cared for.

text:
one of the best decisions i ever made was to stop ‘doing’ family christmases. it was not a healthy environment, i found it deeply stressful to visit my parents house & engage in a charade, a pretense of ‘family’, and so the last christmas i spent in my family home was at age 19, over 30 years ago.
.
just because most people are doing something doesn’t mean it’s healthy, right or good for you.
.
make plans now for the holiday or festive season that feel the best, the most fun & relaxing to & for you. if that’s not spending it with ‘family’ consider making plans that will be extra supportive, consider putting things in place in case it feels challenging or difficult - for those without family, or without good family relationships, christmas & other holidays can be a difficult time - if it’s difficult for you put a strategy in place now to support your mental health then.
.

#christmas #family #stress #rules #rulesforlife #makeplans #plans #planning #selfcare #selflove #noexpectations #chosenfamily #expectations #change #betruetoyourself #support #mentalhealth #mentalhealthawareness #survivaltips #metoo

text:
helsingin sanomat tänään, 15.11.2018❤️❤️ mä oon niin onnellinen et joku muukin vihdoin puhuu avoimesti tästä! mä työskentelin alalla kymmenen vuotta ja vihdoin tänä syksynä tuli mitta täyteen.

mun persettä on puristeltu kun mulla on ollut kädet täynnä likaisia tuoppeja, mun ulkonäköä on "kehuttu" kun oon kaiken kiireen ja paskan keskellä siivonnut oksennuksia, mun aknearpia on haukuttu, kun oon yrittänyt pitää edes jonkinlaista järjestystä yllä mun baaritiskillä. mun työtovereilta ja työnantajalta  on varastettu omaisuutta ihan vaan "huvin" vuoksi. ja kaikki tää sellaisten ihmisten toimesta, jotka eivät edes osaa sanoa "hei" tai "kiitos!" puhumattakaan siitä, että osaisivat odottaa omaa vuoroaan🤯🤬 ois tosi paljon lisää esimerkkejä, mut en mä kaikkee jaksa tänne rustata. mun pointti on, et multa loppu kärsivällisyys, enkä usko olevani ainoa, jolle näin on käynyt. 
yötyö on tutkitusti kuormittavampaa, kuin päivätyö ja pitkät työvuorot ilman säännöllisiä taukoja terveydelle vaarallisia, joten kuka kaipaa keskenkasvuisten asiakkaiden apinoinnin tuomaa lisästressiä? en mä ainakaan. kenekään ei pitäisi joutua kuuntelemaan vittuilua ja kokemaan jatkuvaa huonoa käytöstä omalla työpaikallaan. miksi helvetissä siis ravintolatyöntekijät joutuvat tapakasvattamaan aikuisia ihmisiä?!?! en ymmärrä.

#valomerkki #metoo #youtoo #vattu

text:
today in class we had a deep dive conversation about domestic violence and i realized that a lot people don’t understand it. someone said, “why can’t the person just say no or just leave?” if you can’t understand that then i certainly hope you never do. “i hate bullies” i wish you understood it so much more than that. it’s not bullying it’s about making who you are not exist anymore and becoming the object of the person hurting you through manipulation, mental abuse, sometimes physical violence and destroy your life, controlling everything using fear. “she can’t be a victim of domestic because there was no physical violence” this is so not true at all because to be honest, bones heal, bruises disappear, cuts close but mental wounds don’t close, heal or disappear. the abuse becomes a illness like cancer. it can go into remission, but unless you nurture it or work with it, it comes back and breaks you. it hurts you, it makes you sick, it makes afraid again, it makes cry and wanna give up (don’t). your mind becomes a castle that is filled with water of memories and your chained to the floor. all you can do is keep swimming and stay at the top for air. eventually your muscles get stronger and it becomes easier to stay up but if you give up one day you start to drown. it’s not as easy as leave, don’t think about, don’t let them bully you, don’t talk to them anymore, it’s not that easy. 
but, to anyone in this situation reading this if you understand what it’s like to be in that castle then i beg you please, talk to a crisis counselor (203) 853-0418 (milford), call safe futures (860) 447-0366, call sexual assault crisis center (860) 442-0604. do not let someone do this to you or family (yes, even it’s just happening to you your children are watching and they are seeing your pain which is hurting them too.) please don’t give up your too important and you have a story being told. i love you. -moon “castle in your mind” #metoo #connecticut #domesticviolence #domesticviolenceawareness
name: Moon

울산 성폭력생존자말하기 북토크에 움직씨 창립작 <코끼리 가면>이 초대 받아 연말을 의미있게 보냅니다. 울산은 성폭력 가해자 일인의 고향이기도 해 더 뜻깊은데 울산 아동여성폭력 상담소협의회에서 후원의 의미로 책을 백 권이나 주문해 주셨어요. 처음 있는 코끼리의 대이동에 얼떨떨하네요. 울산상담소시설협의회에서 뜻을 내어 주신 경위는 울산페미니즘기획단 울페기에서 여름 장맛비 이기고 북토크 자리를 마련해 주신 덕분입니다. 서울 한국성폭력상담소와 어느 여성단체에서 받아본 적 없는 사려깊음을 느낍니다. 이런 선의들이 모이면 정말 더는 북펀딩 안 해도 되겠습니다 🐘🐘
.
2018 아동여성폭력예방사업 
움직씨 출판사의 <코끼리 가면> 노유다 작가와 함께하는 성폭력 생존자 말하기 '북토크 '
.
일시 : 2018. 11. 27(화) 14시-
장소 : 울산시청자미디어센터 다목적홀
주최 : 울산상담소시설협의회
지원 : 울산광역시 
신청 문의 : 움직씨 dm
참가비 : 무료 .
.
